-- Zimbabwe Says Anglo Platinum Proposal Acceptable, Mail Reports
-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 2012-04-08T14:59:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/zimbabwe-says-anglo-platinum-proposal-acceptable-mail-reports.html
Anglo American Platinum Ltd. (AMS)  will
sell 51 percent of its Zimbabwean operation to black Zimbabweans
or a government fund for black businessmen, the state-controlled
Sunday Mail said, citing Zimbabwe’s indigenization minister,
Saviour Kasukuwere.  Anglo American Platinum, the world’s biggest miner of the
precious metal, submitted an indigenization plan to the Zimbabwe
government that was acceptable, Kasukuwere was quoted as saying
in the Harare-based newspaper.  Anglo Platinum owns Unki platinum mine in Zimbabwe in
partnership with  Aquarius Platinum Ltd. (AQP)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at  in Harare
at   blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 